  "guide.xpmagic.body.storage": "The XP Keeping Machine is a furnace for experience. Put in a bottle, fuel, a carrier (powder or crystal) and a name key. While the key's owner is online it drains their XP into an XP Cocktail. Drink it to get the XP back.",
  "guide.xpmagic.body.powder": "Memory Powder (cap 10) is XP fuel. The Powder Separator splits it into coarse (5), medium (2) and fine (1) fractions — but only with a Vibration Stand below it (fuel + redstone). The Powder Mixer recombines fractions.",
  "guide.xpmagic.body.crystals": "An explosion fuses Memory Powder into a Memory Crystal (cap 20 + a bonus). Lightning charges a dropped crystal. An anvil shatters it back to powder (lossy). In soul fire a crystal burns down into a Time Crystal → block, wafer, rod.",
  "guide.xpmagic.body.pearl": "The Memory Pearl (cap 40) is the largest store. An enderman killed by a memory-crystal weapon with Saturation drops one. On an anvil, feed the pearl Vindictive Flesh, Nostalgic Coal or Fruit of Knowledge — up to cap 100.",
  "guide.xpmagic.body.gear": "Memory Crystal tools are diamond-tier, +25% damage and fireproof. Sword, pickaxe, axe and shovel evolve via a special recipe and grow from use (kills or mining). Time Crystal armor is fireproof.",
  "guide.xpmagic.body.tree": "With a memory-crystal hoe enchanted with Saturation, till Truth Farmland — only there does Truth Grain grow. Grain → Knowledge Sapling → Tree of Knowledge → Fruit of Knowledge, fuel for pearls.",
  "guide.xpmagic.body.chips": "Start with a Processing Chip and a Memory Chip — machines and the key are built from them. Make an XP Keeping Machine and some Memory Powder, then follow the chapters. Good luck!"
}
